  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="NL">Protecting HR of Ukrainian political pri</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="NL">The goal of the project is to unite the efforts of Ukrainian human rights organizations, as well as establish a dialogue between human rights organizations and state authorities of Ukraine in order to find ways to release and provide legislative settlement to Ukrainians illegally imprisoned for political reasons, and their families as well. By ensuring the work of a unified platform of human rights organizations and maintaining a register of political prosecution of Ukrainian citizens by the Russian authorities, as well as representing and defending the interests of political prisoners in relevant interdepartmental commissions, expert councils, round tables; conducting advo-cacy activities to support political prisoners and promote the law &#x201C;On social and legal protection of people deprived of liberty as a result of armed aggression against Ukraine&#x201D;. Also, the topic of political prisoners is constantly preserved in the informational space due to the weekly program &#x201C;Release our relatives&#x201D; on Hromadske radio, and various publications in the media and posts on social networks.</narrative>
  </description>
